  "text": "The human eye can alter its optical power to hold objects at different distances into sharp focus on the retina. When an object is fixated by the eye, the ciliary muscles are adjusted such that a sharp image is perceived on the retina. The state of the ciliary muscles provides an absolute cue about the distance to the focused object. However, full accommodation response depends on the accommodative stimulus ; that is, responses of ciliary muscles differ between fuzzy and high-contrast stimuli [CITATION_1] .",
